The police report also reveals that Markel's 2008 black Honda Accord was not locked inside the garage, however, it does not indicate where in the garage the father-of-two's body was discovered.

The incident report of the baffling murder notes the specific time that the report was taken and that evidence was collected from multiple locations.

The four-page report is redacted, especially what he appeared to be doing before the incident and what type of gun was used in the shooting.

The report also reveals that the shooting was reporting was first reported by a 72-year-old neighbor, who told the dispatcher he heard a loud bang emanating from Markel's home and then saw a car driving away, 'possibly white or silver'.

