As the investigation gathers pace, police have not ruled out a contract killing and have issued a picture of a white Toyota Prius that was seen close to the crime scene.

'There’s not enough information to suggest that this is a contract murder. It certainly could be,' said ABC News consultant Brad Garrett, a former FBI agent.

'The most likely theory is that it it’s somebody that he knows.'

However, with no suspects being named, the police are being careful not to reveal crucial evidence that they are hopeful the murderer will volunteer and incriminate themselves.

